<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea mauritiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but more slender (leaves mostly &lt;7 cm long) and inflorescence fewer flowered with longer secondary and tertiary peduncles so the inflorescence appears more lax. The two species are not always easily separated but were drscussed in detail by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
(1959b).
</paragraph>
